Subject: [PATCH 3/3] wasm: loosen mGBA factory canvas option to optional+nullable
Author: pi-extension-gba vendor-builder

The upstream @thenick775/mgba hand-written TS declaration at
src/platform/wasm/mgba.d.ts types the `mGBA` factory as:

    export default function mGBA(options: {
      canvas: HTMLCanvasElement;
    }): Promise<mGBAEmulator>;

This is accurate for the upstream (browser-only) build, where consumers
always hand in a real `<canvas>`. Our vendored build (see patch 0001)
adds `node` to ENVIRONMENT, and in Node there is no DOM and no
HTMLCanvasElement. The Node hot path inside mgba.js does not actually
read `options.canvas` -- the core renders into `outputBuffer` which we
expose via `Module.getPixelBuffer()` (patch 0002). The `canvas`
property is browser-only at runtime.

Previously `src/emulator.ts` worked around the type mismatch with a
`canvas: undefined as unknown as HTMLCanvasElement` cast (Escalation
E1 in docs/design/phase-1-emulator.md). That cast lies to the type
system and poisons downstream consumers. This patch narrows the lie
to a single, documented place: the type surface.

The change:

- `canvas: HTMLCanvasElement` -> `canvas?: HTMLCanvasElement | null`.

Optional + nullable covers both call styles (`mGBA({})` and
`mGBA({ canvas: null })`) while still letting browser consumers pass a
real canvas. The property is kept (not removed) because browser
consumers rely on it.

This is a TYPE-SURFACE-ONLY change. The runtime code in pre.js /
mgba.js is untouched -- patch 0001 already handled the Node runtime
environment. Any code paths inside the glue that do
`.canvas.appendChild(...)`-style access remain gated by
ENVIRONMENT_IS_WEB / ENVIRONMENT_IS_WORKER and are left alone.

Apply with: patch -p1 < 0003-loosen-canvas-type.patch
Base commit: thenick775/mgba @ be30a34e913da1ba7f040d3db4e10f700ce49f76
Depends on: 0001-add-node-environment.patch (for Node runtime).

---
 src/platform/wasm/mgba.d.ts | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/src/platform/wasm/mgba.d.ts
+++ b/src/platform/wasm/mgba.d.ts
@@ -557,6 +557,6 @@
    */
   // eslint-disable-next-line import/no-default-export
   export default function mGBA(options: {
-    canvas: HTMLCanvasElement;
+    canvas?: HTMLCanvasElement | null;
   }): Promise<mGBAEmulator>;
 }
